author: mamta
msg: Rather than quiting out of ClientThread for InterruptedException and IOException, we should first check if the exceptions aree raised because of server being shutdown. If yes, then we should quit out of ClientThread. Otherwise, we should log the exception and close the client socket that got the exception and go back to the infinite loop waiting for next client connection.

author: trawick
msg: FcgidCmdOptions didn't work when a wrapper was defined with cmd-line arguments
(e.g., FcgidWrapper "/path/to/php -c /path/to/ini" .php) as it tried to look
up the entire command-line in the cmd options hash.
Change FcgidWrapper to save the executable file name it already computes
for use later when looking up the wrapper in the cmd options hash.
